reviews.review_text: A Good Mix For A Good Show. But... As a serious audience maven, I prefer the natural sound of the other gd89-04-17.aud.wiley.9207.sbeok.shnf upload. It's absolutely KILLER!!! One of the best audience recordings I have ever heard.  So check out my review of that primo capture and I'll try to Dropbox the show to you in MP3 that I remixed with Mike Darby's crowd.  This SBD's vocals are a little to high and stark in the mix for me, where they mesh much better in the ID-9207 DFC FOB version.
Brilliant Love me a Seamons matrix, especially when it's the last show the Dead ever played in my home state of Minnesota. Like the show a bunch as well.
